    "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::pass_through_facades_and_wide_function_bags::dedd268a",
    "summary": "Multiple layers add indirection without policy, while very wide function-bag runtimes leak internal detail instead of defining crisp contracts.",
    "detail": {
      "holistic": true,
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/auth/auth.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/orchestration.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go",
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/container_bridge.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`auth/auth.go` primarily forwards calls directly to other packages with minimal added behavior.",
        "`orchestration/orchestration.go` mirrors lifecycle and registry methods through thin wrappers.",
        "`runtime_ops.go` exposes broad dependency bags with many function fields, and `container_bridge.go` performs repetitive field-by-field adaptation."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Collapse pure pass-through APIs, split runtime contracts by bounded workflow, and keep adapters at module edges where they enforce policy/translation rather than mirroring internals.",
      "reasoning": ""
    }
  },
